@startuml
title Password Recovery & Authentication

actor User as user
participant "<<interface>>\nForgotPassword\nScreen" as forgot #A9C4E9
participant "<<control>>\nAuth Service\n(Supabase)" as auth #FDB983
participant "<<service>>\nSMTP\nMail Server" as smtp #C5E0B4
participant "<<interface>>\nOTP Verification\nScreen" as otp #A9C4E9
participant "<<interface>>\nResetPassword\nScreen" as reset #A9C4E9
participant "<<entity>>\nauth.users\n(PostgreSQL)" as db #FFE599

== Step 1: Request Password Reset ==
user -> forgot: 1 Enter professional email
forgot -> auth: 2 resetPasswordForEmail(email, type: OTP)
auth -> smtp: 3 Send OTP code email
smtp --> user: 4 Deliver Password Reset OTP to inbox

== Step 2: OTP Verification ==
user -> otp: 5 Enter OTP code from email
alt incorrect or expired
    otp -> auth: 6 verifyOTP(email, token, type: recovery)
    auth --> otp: 7 Error — invalid or expired OTP
    otp --> user: 8 Display error, allow retry
else valid
    otp -> auth: 9 verifyOTP(email, token, type: recovery)
    auth --> otp: 10 OTP verified — session initialized
    otp -> reset: 11 Navigate to password reset screen
end

== Step 3: Password Update ==
user -> reset: 12 Enter and confirm new password
reset -> auth: 13 updatePassword(newPassword)
auth -> db: 14 UPDATE auth.users SET password = hashed
db --> auth: 15 Success
auth --> reset: 16 Password updated confirmation
reset --> user: 17 Display success dialog

@enduml